1. Download the software:  

Link â€“ > https://www.enterprisedb.com/downloads/postgres-postgresql-downloads

2. Start the downloaded executable:
    - install directory:   eg.  /Library/PostgreSQL/14
    - choose components
    - data  directory:   eg.  /Library/PostgreSQL/14/data
    - password
    - port: 5432
    - Locale: default
    
3. Validate the installation:
$ ps -ef | grep postgres

4. Now login with postgres user and connect to server for validation:
./psql -d postgres -U postgres
=# select datname from pg_database;
